<h2>
    Top Fishing Spots near Portland, Oregon
</h2>
<h3>
    Clackamas River
</h3>
<p>
    A local favorite, the <strong>Clackamas River</strong> is home to wild and stocked brown trout. The river has easy access points and deep pools perfect for drift fishing.
</p>
<h3>
    Wilson River
</h3>
<p>
    Located about an hour west, this river offers clear waters and a tranquil setting. Best fished in spring and fall with flies or small spoons.
</p>
<h3>
    Sandy River
</h3>
<p>
    Closer to Mount Hood, this glacier-fed river supports seasonal brown trout along with steelhead. Fish the deeper runs and undercut banks.
</p>
<h3>
    Trillium Lake
</h3>
<p>
    A scenic spot with a backdrop of Mount Hood, this lake is great for kayak fishing and has solid trout action from April to October.
</p>
<h3>
    Henry Hagg Lake
</h3>
<p>
    Popular for family fishing trips, Hagg Lake is regularly stocked. Use bait from the bank or fish deep with lures from a boat.
</p>
